values: Well, my side of the room is nearly empty.  It has been a fun year, but I am looking forward to more...especially with the girls.  I can't wait to be home tomorrow!!!  Mom, sister, dad, bro..BEACH..slurpees..Da Kine..Charlie & Jake's..church..Julie Anne..Regina, Beth, Katie, Danni, Nicole..only one more night in SG 007!!
http://uhrainuh.livejournal.com/6016.html

So yes, definitel nostalgia today.  I was packing up my room since my parents came to take stuff.  I had to pack up clothes, the took the tv and fridge.  As I was taking down pictures, I started to think about the past year.  So much has happened-good and bad.  I have grown so much as a person I feel like.  I have made a whole new set of best friends.  These people I want to know forever.  When I am old, they are the people I hope I am sitting on my porch with, ya know?  They are the people I want in or at my wedding, they are people that I want my kids to know and love.  Now I am thinking about how, after next year, I don't know what will happen with all of us.  Next year will def. be fun.  I love the girls so much.  They have made this year so fun, interesting, dramatic (hehe), and the best I could ever have imagined!

Why don't people see things outside of themselves?  Being able to see outside the box, or to put yourself in other people's shoes, or to see things from an outside perspective is key.  I guess sometimes people just can't do that.  There are things that I just don't understand.  I guess the way that you are raised makes up who you are.  Lack of a father (among other things), makes for big attachment to the first guy that shows ANY interest.  Twenty year old guys don't want to settle down with girls 9 states a way..most of the time.  Everyone has different feelings, ones that no one else will understand, I suppose...however, sometimes you DO need to listen to others and re-evaluate a situation.  Take it for what it WAS, not what you thought it was, could be, or what you WANTED it to be...

Cancer Drinking style: Cancer is a comfort drinker -- and an extra wine
with dinner or an after-work beer or six can be
extra comforting, can't it, Cancer darling?
Like fellow water signs Scorpio and Pisces,
Crabs must guard against lushery. Cancers are
brilliant at ferreting out secret parties and
insinuating themselves on VIP lists -- and, in
true Hollywood style, Cancers are never really
drunk; instead, they get "tired and
emotional" (read: weepy when lubricated).
But there's nothing better than swapping
stories (and spit) over a few bottles of inky
red wine with your favorite Cancer. Even your
second-favorite Cancer will do. The sign also
rules the flavor vanilla, and you'd be adored
if you served up vanilla vodka and soda.

So I feel like lately I have really been missing out on a boyfriend or someone to be dating.  Usually it doesn't bother me..but lately, I dunno..it just has.  I mean, it definitely doesn't consume me or anything like that.  I think it's just because there is a new guy that could potentially be interested.  He seems good and is friends with a couple of my friends.  I guess he isn't my "type" although I guess I don't really have a type.  I feel like I really want things to work out or for SOMETHING to happen anyway.  He just seems very nonchalant about everything, like just very chill, which is a good thing, but it makes him hard to read.  Sooo, I don't know if he isn't interested or if it's that he just doesn't know me enough...I'm hoping it's the latter of the two.  Oh well, who knows..I'm not getting my hopes up because that just doesn't help anything.  I'll just try to hang out with him and talk to him more.  Bowling is good.  Grab-a-date I had to be flirty and cute..SOBER!  I'm glad I gave up alcohol but even more glad that Sarah gave it up with me!  When I was thinking about it before, being the only sober one sucks, but if I have a buddy it'll be totally fine.  So that was good news.  Anyway, thoughts about everything are scattered..I'm being a schizo!
